title: For Sale:  AR15-PLUM CRAZY LOWER/CMMG GAS PISTON UPPER
postcontent:
Hello and welcome to my ad...

I am one of a few FFL'S in Arizona that carry and believe in the Plum Crazy Composite Lower Receiver.I have several in stock as of this writing.

Today, I am pairing up the Plum Crazy Lower receiver with the CMMG M4-LEP II UPPER WITH Gas Piston System

Gas Piston systems operate cleaner then the direct gas impingement operating systems. With the piston system, the propellant gases that are being diverted at the gas block are now vented at the gas block, instead in the operating system of the upper receiver. Since the fouling from the gas system is not being vented in to the action of your firearm, it stays cooler and cleaner. Our system is designed around the short stroke piston operation. The piston pushes the anti tilt one piece carrier, which unlocks the bolt and allows the piston to return home while the bolt carrier continues to cycle independently. The upper is built off of our standard forged A3 receiver with M4 feed ramps. The chrome plated gas piston is mounted in a solid one piece steel gas block attached to the barrel by pins. The Gas Block's 1913 Piccatinny rail is receiver height and requires a front sight designed to be mounted on the same plane as the rear sight. The dedicated, piston specific, anti-tilt bolt carrier is one piece, machined with the piston impingement key(not a bolt on). The carrier uses our standard Mil-Spec bolt. The barrel is our 4140 steel, M4 profile, 5.56mm chamber and bore, 1/9 twist ratio and 1/2x28 threaded barrel and our proprietary WASP surface treatment. The upper is finished with M4 handguard caps, M4 handguards and an A2 flash hider installed with a crush washer. The piston gas block has a gas shut off setting for use with a suppressor to allow for maximum noise reduction. You must replace the crush washer with a peel washer if you plan to mount your suppressor on the original flash hider. Fits on any standard Mil-Spec lower receiver. All uppers have been factory head spaced and test fired. There are no upgrade options available with this model. Nickel Teflon bolt carriers are discontinued and now come with a phosphated carrier. 



The Plum Crazy Complete Lower Assembly with 6-position collapible stock is engineered using fiber reinforced composite material,more resilient to damage than aluminum.These lower receivers have been extensively tested and proven.HF,FN and Glock all use polymers to bring their products into the new millennium.Now there is an AR-15 that sets the standard for the next generation of shooting enthusiasts.1-weighs approximately half that of forged aluminum.2-durability surpasses forged aluminum.3-impervious to chemicals including acids,fuels, and salts.4-reduced wear properties and no color loss from wear.5-engineered for acceptance of Mil-Spec Parts(less winter trigger)

My price is out the door! 

I run my business,Crazzy Joes,out of my house in Arizona City and I am an authorized dealer for the Plum Crazy Lower Receiver.If interested,respond to this ad.If you want to call me,dial REDACTED or REDACTED.I work in Phoenix Mon-Fri and would be willing to meet.

I require a AZ.DL and CCW.If no CCW,I would have to run an ATF background check to make purchase legal.This price is out the door.I currently only have this one configuration at this price.Working on a second will post later.Cash sale only.
